The President of the United States gave a statement addressing the ongoing federal response to the violence in Charlottesville, Virginia. He condemned the display of hatred, bigotry, and violence, stating that it has no place in America. He emphasized that racism is evil and those who cause violence in its name are criminals. The Department of Justice has opened a civil rights investigation into the car attack that killed one person and injured 20 others. The President expressed grief for the victims and their families, and praised the law enforcement agencies for their efforts in restoring law and order. He also discussed his economic agenda, including trade policy and tax cuts. The President concluded by emphasizing the importance of love, unity, and justice in the face of hate and violence.